feat: cancel agent at next tool call. The stop button now sends POST /conversations/{id}/stop?agent_id=X which (1) sets processing_status to idle so the processor loop stops, (2) calls POST /v1/cancel on the agent's harness which writes a .cancel flag file in WORKSPACE_DIR. The MCP tool dispatcher (mcp_xpressclaw.py) checks for the flag before every tools/call — if found, removes it and returns a cancellation error telling the agent to stop. The flag is cleared at harness startup to prevent stale flags from previous runs. The cancel is per-agent (thinkingAgent from the frontend), not broadcast to all participants.
